definition.value: A nuclear magnetic resonance setting is a setting that specifies some configuration of a nuclear magnetic resonance spectrometer. [Allotrope]
A spectral width setting is a nuclear magnetic resonance setting that describes the range over which data is to be collected. [Allotrope]

A pulse sequence setting is a nuclear magnetic resonance setting that describes a series of radio frequency pulses applied to the sample, such that the free induction decay is related to the characteristic frequencies of the desired signals. [Wikipedia]

A pulse duration setting is a nuclear magnetic resonance setting that specifies the duration of time the NMR applies the radio pulse per scan in order to flip the spin states of the active nuclei to be measured. [Allotrope]

A relaxation delay setting is a nuclear magnetic resonance setting that specifies the duration of time the NMR allocates for the nuclei spin states to return to their original state after being exposed to the radio pulse. [Allotrope]

A presaturation frequency setting is a nuclear magnetic resonance setting that specifies the frequency of an initial low power pulse generally applied to suppress the signal associated with the solvent. [Allotrope]

label.value: free induction decay spectrum data cube

definition.value: A free induction decay spectrum data cube is a data cube that is a representation of a free induction decay spectrum. [Allotrope]

A free induction decay spectrum is a nuclear magnetic resonance spectrum that quantifies the combined decay of aligned nuclear spins after excitation with a short radio-frequency pulse (data before the Fourier transform to the frequency domain). [Allotrope]
A zero-order phase adjustment setting is a data processing setting to counter the linear phase shift effect of delay time Î´ on an NMR signal. [Allotrope]

A first-order phase adjustment setting is a data processing setting to counter the effect that different resonances in a spectrum may not experience the same flip angle from magnetization. [Allotrope]
An NMR multiplet aggregate document is a document that aggregates NMR multiplet documents. [Allotrope]
An NMR multiplet document is a document that encompasses the information associated with an NMR multiplet. [Allotrope]
An NMR multiplet type is a classification datum that classifies a multiplet in a nuclear magnetic resonance assay. [Allotrope]
A J-coupling aggregate document is a document that aggregates J-coupling documents. [Allotrope]
A J-coupling document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a J-coupling. [Allotrope]
An inversion enabled setting is a data processing setting specifying if a complex-conjugate of the data is performed before the protocol and FT is applied. [Allotrope]
A data shuffling algorithm setting is a data processing setting specifying the algorithm used to process phase sensitive two-dimensional spectra. [Allotrope]

A quadrature setting is a data processing setting to distinguish the negative frequencies from the positive ones by the detection and summation of the in-phase and ninety degree out-of-phase magnetizations (two-channel mode). [Allotrope]
A real Fourier transform enabled setting is a data processing setting specifying that a real Fourier Transform is executed as opposed to the conventional Discreet Fourier Transform. [Allotrope]

A swap IR II enabled setting is a data processing setting specifying that the IR and II quadrants are swapped before performing the Fourier transform to cover Relay_CH coefficients 1 0 1 0 0 1 0 1. [Allotrope]

A change II sign enabled setting is a data processing setting specifying that the sign of the II quadrant is flipped before the Fourier transform to cover Relay_2CH coefficients 1 0 -1 0 0 1 0 -1. [Allotrope]
A nuclear magnetic resonance tube document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a nuclear magnetic resonance tube. [Allotrope]

A relative abundance is a quality quantification facet quantifying the relative number of atoms of a particular isotope in a mixture of the isotope of an element, expressed as a fraction of all the atoms of the element. [Allotrope]
An expected peak position is a prediction that indicates the position of a peak as predicted by theory and/or historical data. [Allotrope]
A frequency setting is a setting that specifies some frequency. [Allotrope]
A maximum frequency setting is a setting that specifies the upper limit of some frequency. [Allotrope]
A minimum frequency setting is a setting that specifies the lower limit of some frequency. [Allotrope]

label.value: multi-dimensional free induction decay spectrum data cube

definition.value: A multi-dimensional free induction decay spectrum data cube is a representation of a free induction decay spectrum with more than one dimension. [Allotrope]

label.value: multi-dimensional nuclear magnetic resonance spectrum data cube

definition.value: A multi-dimensional nuclear magnetic resonance spectrum data cube is a representation of a nuclear magnetic resonance spectrum with more than one dimension. [Allotrope]
A dimension type is a classification datum that classifies a dimension as directly or indirectly measured. [Allotrope]
A dimension identifier is an identifier that identifies some dimension. [Allotrope]
A J-coupling constant is a data region facet that quantifies the horizontal distance on a spectrum between two peaks in the same NMR multiplet. [Allotrope]
A data region identifier is an identifier that identifies some data region. [Allotrope]
A data region name is a written name that denotes some data region. [Allotrope]
A data region start is a data region facet that denotes the first value of the abscissa that belongs to the region. [Allotrope]
A data region end is a data region facet that denotes the last value of the abscissa that belongs to the region. [Allotrope]
A data region area is a data region facet that quantitates the area enclosed by a data region and the selected baseline. [Allotrope]
A relative data region area is a data region facet that denotes the area of the data region relative to some other region or summation of regions. [Allotrope]

label.value: baseline value at start of data region

definition.value: A baseline value at start of data region is a data region facet that denotes the ordinate value of the baseline of a data region at the region start. [Allotrope]

label.value: baseline value at end of data region

definition.value: A baseline value at end of data region is a data region facet that denotes the ordinate value of the baseline of a data region at the region end. [Allotrope]
A data region value at start is a data region facet that denotes the first value of the ordinate that belongs to the region. [Allotrope]
A data region value at end is a data region facet that denotes the last value of the ordinate that belongs to the region. [Allotrope]
An electrophoresis aggregate document is a document that aggregates electrophoresis documents. [Allotrope]
An electrophoresis document is a document that encompasses the information associated with an electrophoresis run. [Allotrope]
An electropherogram data cube is a data cube that represents an electropherogram. [Allotrope]
A derived electropherogram is derived from the outcome of an electrophoresis run and reports the response of the detector as a function of a derived unit. [Allotrope]
A derived electropherogram data cube is a data cube that represents a derived electropherogram. [Allotrope]
A polymer length is a length datum that quantifies the length of some polymer. [Allotrope]
A data region facet is a facet that is part of a data region. [Allotrope]

A data region describes a part of a data distribution function at a definite range of the experimental parameter (independent variable) of the distribution function. This definition includes a single data point of the distribution function. [Allotrope]
